Sentencas: The mismatch of the coefficients of thermal expansion between cathode and electrolyte is one of the thorniest problems for high-performance proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H-SOFCs).
Titulo: Y2Mo3O12-Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode catalyst for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here one strategy is applied by introducing the negative thermal expansion component, Y2Mo3O12 (YMO), on Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) cathode to overcome this difficulty.
Titulo: Y2Mo3O12-Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode catalyst for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As a result, not only the electrolyte-cathode connection but also the cell performance is improved.
Titulo: Y2Mo3O12-Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode catalyst for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the cell using a composite cathode reaches 1010.9 mW cm-2 at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Y2Mo3O12-Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode catalyst for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The YMO softens the stress on the contact layer that keeps the cathode from delamination, which is confirmed by simulation studies and experiments.
Titulo: Y2Mo3O12-Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode catalyst for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the A-site defect on BSCF created by the reaction between YMO and BSCF also plays a positive role in the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity.
Titulo: Y2Mo3O12-Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode catalyst for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This study provided a new way to study and improve the thermo-mechanical stability and cell performance of H-SOFCs.
Titulo: Y2Mo3O12-Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode catalyst for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
